node.title: first-class git
node.description: Make git remote install things more first-class so that they behave in less unpredictable ways.

* handles scoped packages
* allows passing parameters to `npm run-script` scripts
* works with npm Enterprise

node.title: cache rewrite
node.description:
1. extract the caching code into a standalone package
2. make the core of the cache a content-addressable store
3. improve `npm shrinkwrap` to take advantage of shasum-based cache
4. read-through web-style cache completely decoupled from installer and the rest of the CLI (except `npm-registry-client`)

node.title: 4.x
node.description: There are a number of smaller but still breaking issues popping up. We're targeting a mid-February release of `npm@4.0.0`, which includes these small but breaking changes. It's not intended to be another big-bang release. Unless Node 6 forks by then, `npm@3` will not be included as an npm LTS release series, so at that point the team will be supporting only `npm@2` and `npm@4`.

node.title: files and ignores
node.description: Milestone for bugfixes and features related to hashing out specifics of how files get packaged or excluded
